   
<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph  >
This sample illustrates how to use the ComboBox with multiple selections and how to set the Default Text and Selection value Delimiter.
</Paragraph>
  <Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center"><Image Source="Images\comboboxdemo.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">
Interactive Features
</TextBlock >
</BlockUIContainer>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Allow Multi Selection    :</Bold> Multiple items can be selected. </Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Selection value Delimiter :</Bold> Selected items values separated by given delimiter string.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Default Text              :</Bold> It is possible to display default text when no items selected</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


</FlowDocument>
